															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser deleted" data-id="1313607"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/common--images/avatars/default/a16.png" alt=""/>(account deleted)</span> <span class="odate time_1362183574 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">02 Mar 2013 00:19</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1722307">
									

<p>There's almost a bit&#8230; too much of a reveal, here? And it gets a little muddled around the middle bit, when they're hiding in the bathroom, but I still read the entire thing without feeling bored and rather enjoyed the mundane psychological treatment of the wacky supernatural.</p>
<p>There are some very stilted phrases, though:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>One thing I have yet to understand till this day is Sara's definition of any word used to positively describe any given thing.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>this sentence makes almost no sense&#8212; did you mean &quot;'cute', it wasn't&quot; or &quot;I'll never understand the way Sara saw the world, if that was her idea of 'cute'&quot;</p>
<blockquote>
<p>his incisive claws</p>
</blockquote>
<p>probably not the modifier you want to use</p>
<blockquote>
<p>expressing how scared of it I was</p>
</blockquote>
<p>&quot;I told her it was terrifying&quot;</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Her pale face was carrying an expression of pure dread.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>anything variation that doesn't involve &quot;face was carrying and expression of&quot;</p>
<p>your verb tense also changes up a few times&#8212; between &quot;it's been a few hours&quot; and &quot;William was&quot;; is this present or past?</p>

							</div>

								
					
