					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/causticbotanist" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1635334); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1635334&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610250576" alt="CausticBotanist" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1635334)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/causticbotanist" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1635334); return false;" >CausticBotanist</a></span> <span class="odate time_1419203612 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">21 Dec 2014 23:13</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2186000">
									

<p>While I enjoyed the premise of this, I can't help but feel annoyed by some grammatical oversights. The psychiatry session is pretty jumbled, usually when somebody has different characters speaking they create a new paragraph, even if for a few lines. Also some sentences didn't really make sense to me. Like; &quot; I was more concerned about trying to calm her down by telling her that maybe they weren't really there than I was about seeing Capone in the mirror.&quot; Are you saying he was trying to calm her down, than suddenly saw Capone in the mirror? So unfortunately I downvoted it.</p>
<p>I will say this though, even though I downvoted this, I admire your &quot;Pitch Haven&quot; series SCP's and look completely forward to the tales that you will make on it.</p>

							</div>

								
					
